            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Benji Feldman\u2019s story didn\u2019t begin in the moody glow of a San Francisco cocktail bar, but under the relentless sun of the East Bay suburbs. Raised by a pragmatic accountant father and a nurturing elementary school teacher, his childhood was stable and loving, but it hummed with an unspoken expectation of a traditional life path: college, a 9-to-5 job, a house with a lawn.\n\nHe tried. He enrolled at San Francisco State, pursuing a vague Liberal Arts degree, but found himself more captivated by the city's pulse than his philosophy lectures. To fund his studies and city living, he took a job as a barback in North Beach. It was a revelation. Amidst the clatter of ice, the complex alchemy of spirits, and the low hum of human stories being shared over a glass, he found a classroom that felt more real and vital than any lecture hall. After two years, he dropped out of college, a decision that quietly disappointed his parents but felt to Benji like an essential act of self-discovery.\n\nHis career became his education. Benji\u2019s ascent was a slow, deliberate distillation of skill. He worked his way up from barback to bartender, moving from loud tourist spots to respectable restaurants, absorbing every lesson on technique, history, and the art of listening. Now, as the Lead Mixologist and Bar Manager at a sophisticated Hayes Valley establishment, he\u2019s a craftsman. He\u2019s known for his innovative cocktails that often incorporate historical recipes and locally foraged ingredients.\n\nBenji\u2019s life is hyper-local. He lives in a small but well-appointed apartment just a few blocks from work, his 0.8-mile commute a daily walking meditation through the neighborhood he considers his village. He knows the baristas, the bookstore clerks, and the chefs at neighboring restaurants by name. This deep-rooted community is his anchor in a city often defined by transience. After a serious long-term relationship ended in his early thirties, he has found contentment in a rich social life built around industry peers and loyal regulars.\n\nHis ultimate dream is to own his own place. Not a sprawling club, but an intimate, 20-seat bar dedicated to impeccable drinks and genuine connection\u2014a true reflection of the craft and community he has dedicated his life to building in the heart of San Francisco."
